******
[2] Nigeria (Gombe)
Date: Wed 11 Aug 2021
Source: Vanguard News [edited]
https://www.vanguardngr.com/2021/08/gombe-records-44-cholera-cases-with-4-deaths-commissioner/


Gombe commissioner for health, Dr Habu Dahiru, says 4 persons have died, with 44 others testing positive for cholera out of the 77 gastroenteritis cases recorded in the state. Dahiru disclosed this at a news conference on Tuesday [10 Aug 2021] in Gombe. According to him, government has already placed 3 settlements in the state capital on red alert, namely, Shamaki, Bolari-East, and Herwagana wards of Gombe local government area (LGA).

The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) had reported that the state had, within the 1st and 2nd quarters, announced an outbreak of cholera in Yalmatu Deba and Akko LGAs, with 178 persons treated and discharged, while 2 children reportedly died.

"We now have a total of 77 cases of gastroenteritis and 48 of them have been confirmed to be positive for cholera. Out of the 77 cases, we lost 4 patients from the 48 positive cholera cases. With the threshold of confirmed cases reached, I hereby declare an outbreak of cholera in Shamaki, Bolari-East and Herwagana wards of Gombe LGA," he announced. He emphasized the need for personal hygiene, noting that water collected from wells must be filtered while vegetables should be washed with vinegar or saltwater before consumption.

According to him, the ministry is working with the Ministry of Environment and Water Resources to mitigate it. Dahiru further said that government had designated a temporary treatment and rehydration centre for cholera in Gombe LGA at the Tudun-Wada Primary Healthcare Centre.

